turning off the practice room lights)

2449
01:18:59,392 --> 01:19:00,448
JUSTIN: I should eat too.

2450
01:19:00,900 --> 01:19:03,100
(Also grabbing the empty drink cans before leaving)

2451
01:19:03,500 --> 01:19:05,248
(Wrapping up this long day)

2452
01:19:05,248 --> 01:19:06,656
TRAINEE: Kyaaah.

2453
01:19:07,700 --> 01:19:12,600
(Meanwhile, HARUTA addicted to the Superman song)

2454
01:19:12,633 --> 01:19:15,040
(Humming while writing in the diary)
HARUTA: SUPER JUNIOR is...

2455
01:19:15,040 --> 01:19:16,833
HARUTA: SUPER JUNIOR is...

2456
01:19:17,152 --> 01:19:18,766
HAMIN: Did you write that we got first place?

2457
01:19:18,866 --> 01:19:19,766
HARUTA: Ah, I didn't.

2458
01:19:19,800 --> 01:19:22,176
HAMIN: Oh, what are you doing?
You should write it in here.

2459
01:19:23,264 --> 01:19:24,608
HARUTA: Did I show it to you?

2460
01:19:24,608 --> 01:19:25,568
HARUTA: The drawing I made of you.

2461
01:19:25,760 --> 01:19:27,072
HAMIN: Me? No.

2462
01:19:27,744 --> 01:19:28,640
HARUTA: Ah, here it is.

2463
01:19:29,312 --> 01:19:31,433
(Shows HAMIN on the first day's diary)
HARUTA: Wanna see?

2464
01:19:31,433 --> 01:19:33,248
(HAMIN that I took)

2465
01:19:33,248 --> 01:19:35,296
HAMIN: Hahaha.

2466
01:19:37,376 --> 01:19:37,984
HARUTA: Haha.

2467
01:19:40,200 --> 01:19:42,133
HAMIN: Isn't this like an anti-fan thing?

2468
01:19:42,300 --> 01:19:43,648
(He grumbles but still takes the picture)

2469
01:19:43,648 --> 01:19:44,896
HAMIN: What's this?

2470
01:19:46,033 --> 01:19:48,800
HARUTA: This was the most memorable on the first day.

2471
01:19:49,333 --> 01:19:52,866
(Going along with it,
mimicking HAMIN's intro song pose)

2472
01:19:52,866 --> 01:19:55,400
HAMIN: I have to stay still in this pose,
so it's a bit embarrassing.

2473
01:19:55,904 --> 01:19:56,608
HAMIN: Kind of...

2474
01:19:57,133 --> 01:19:59,233
HARUTA: We definitely didn't do this at the company.

2475
01:19:59,533 --> 01:20:01,333
HARUTA: I was wondering what this person is doing.

2476
01:20:01,333 --> 01:20:02,566
HARUTA: And I was watching it.

2477
01:20:03,400 --> 01:20:07,800
(Gradually, friends started gathering one by one)
TRAINEE: SIWON is really handsome.

2478
01:20:07,800 --> 01:20:09,566
HAMIN: Ah, and they were really kind.

2479
01:20:10,133 --> 01:20:12,600
HAMIN: They were so good, I'm totally jealous.

2480
01:20:13,133 --> 01:20:16,900
HAMIN: I've watched so many videos
of SUPER JUNIOR seniors.

2481
01:20:16,900 --> 01:20:20,400
HAMIN: Their personalities were
exactly the same as on variety shows.

2482
01:20:20,400 --> 01:20:24,833
HAMIN: SIWON came over
and gave high-fives even from afar.

2483
01:20:24,833 --> 01:20:27,300
HAMIN: He came to each of us one by one like this.

2484
01:20:27,300 --> 01:20:29,900
HAMIN: "Oh, JAEWON, oh, JUSTIN," like this...

2485
01:20:29,900 --> 01:20:31,700
HAMIN: He did all this.

2486
01:20:31,700 --> 01:20:34,300
HAMIN: And also said, "Be confident."

2487
01:20:34,966 --> 01:20:37,033
HAMIN: Moments like that
made me think, "Wow, this is real."

2488
01:20:37,433 --> 01:20:39,766
HAMIN: And he really likes SHINDONG.

2489
01:20:39,766 --> 01:20:42,000
HAMIN: So he stayed by his side the whole time.

2490
01:20:42,240 --> 01:20:43,366
JUSTIN: How did you know?

2491
01:20:43,366 --> 01:20:45,200
HAMIN: From his expression.

2492
01:20:45,200 --> 01:20:46,200
JUSTIN: I couldn't stop looking at him.

2493
01:20:46,366 --> 01:20:47,233
HAMIN: When we first held hands...

2494
01:20:47,233 --> 01:20:48,433
HAMIN: When holding hands in a circle,

2495
01:20:49,766 --> 01:20:52,096
(Getting excited following the excited JUSTIN)
HAMIN: he was so excited.

2496
01:20:52,096 --> 01:20:52,704
JUSTIN: But then, what's that...

2497
01:20:53,133 --> 01:20:54,566
JAEWON: But what I always think is,

2498
01:20:54,566 --> 01:20:55,072
JAEWON: like...

2499
01:20:55,072 --> 01:20:57,216
JAEWON: when we debut,

2500
01:20:57,760 --> 01:20:58,816
JAEWON: twenty years later,

2501
01:20:59,488 --> 01:21:01,376
JAEWON: we'll probably
be telling the next generation...

2502
01:21:01,920 --> 01:21:02,720
HAMIN: Hmm.

2503
01:21:03,808 --> 01:21:04,864
HAMIN: The same stories.

2504
01:21:05,440 --> 01:21:08,533
JAEWON: Just imagining it made me so thrilled.

2505
01:21:09,300 --> 01:21:13,366
(At that moment, NICHOLAS just finished showering)

2506
01:21:14,000 --> 01:21:17,433
(Attempts to quietly write a diary)

2507
01:21:17,866 --> 01:21:20,966
(Though the diary is open)

2508
01:21:21,833 --> 01:21:26,100
(Unable to write easily)

2509
01:21:28,100 --> 01:21:29,696
(In the lounge this morning)
NICHOLAS: Oh, dear.

2510
01:21:30,592 --> 01:21:31,552
SONGHA: Huh?

2511
01:21:32,064 --> 01:21:34,624
(SONGHA and NICHOLAS woke up
early due to another shoot)

2512
01:21:34,688 --> 01:21:35,648
SONGHA: Hey.

2513
01:21:35,904 --> 01:21:37,728
SONGHA: NICHOLAS.

2514
01:21:37,984 --> 01:21:39,616
SONGHA: I'm genuinely curious about something.

2515
01:21:40,766 --> 01:21:43,033
SONGHA: Honestly, until now, I hadn't asked directly,

2516
01:21:43,233 --> 01:21:45,333
SONGHA: but I had a rough idea.

2517
01:21:45,440 --> 01:21:48,224
SONGHA: You, an idol...

2518
01:21:48,896 --> 01:21:49,888
NICHOLAS: Not gonna do it?

2519
01:21:50,240 --> 01:21:52,480
SONGHA: Anyway.

2520
01:21:52,900 --> 01:21:55,166
SONGHA: I knew for a long time

2521
01:21:55,166 --> 01:21:57,533
SONGHA: that you wanted to do something else.

2522
01:21:59,520 --> 01:22:00,224
NICHOLAS: Honestly,

2523
01:22:00,633 --> 01:22:02,466
NICHOLAS: I thought

2524
01:22:02,466 --> 01:22:04,566
NICHOLAS: a lot about when I should say it.

2525
01:22:04,896 --> 01:22:06,112
NICHOLAS: "I only want to be an actor."

2526
01:22:06,112 --> 01:22:08,608
(Hesitated for a long time about wanting to be an actor)
NICHOLAS: I hesitated for a long time before saying that.

2527
01:22:13,233 --> 01:22:13,952
(Today afternoon, after the sports day)

2528
01:22:13,952 --> 01:22:14,816
TRAINEE: Oh, good job.

2529
01:22:14,816 --> 01:22:15,968
SIWON: NICHOLAS, NICHOLAS.

2530
01:22:16,733 --> 01:22:18,766
SIWON: From what I've seen, you seem to
have a lot on your mind too, right?

2531
01:22:19,300 --> 01:22:20,256
(SIWON noticed NICHOLAS' worries and dreams)
SIWON: Do you want to act,

2532
01:22:20,256 --> 01:22:21,760
SIWON: or do you want to be a singer later?

2533
01:22:21,760 --> 01:22:22,432
NICHOLAS: I want to act.

2534
01:22:22,432 --> 01:22:23,104
SIWON: You want to act?

2535
01:22:23,360 --> 01:22:24,633
SIWON: Oh.

2536
01:22:24,633 --> 01:22:26,466
SIWON: Why? Is there a specific reason?

2537
01:22:26,466 --> 01:22:28,466
NICHOLAS: Back in high school,

2538
01:22:28,733 --> 01:22:30,400
NICHOLAS: we had separate acting classes.

2539
01:22:30,400 --> 01:22:31,232
SIWON: Yeah?

2540
01:22:31,232 --> 01:22:31,872
NICHOLAS: Yes.

2541
01:22:31,872 --> 01:22:33,333
NICHOLAS: So at that time,

2542
01:22:33,792 --> 01:22:36,224
(After watching Benedict Cumberbatch's play 'Frankenstein')
NICHOLAS: I watched 'Frankenstein' as a play.

2543
01:22:36,224 --> 01:22:36,672
- SIWON: Really?
- NICHOLAS: Benedict Cumberbatch's

2544
01:22:36,672 --> 01:22:38,533
NICHOLAS: 'Frankenstein' thing.

2545
01:22:38,533 --> 01:22:41,024
(The dream of acting began like that)
NICHOLAS: After seeing that, I became...

2546
01:22:41,024 --> 01:22:42,048
- SIWON: Oh, really?
- NICHOLAS: really passionate

2547
01:22:42,048 --> 01:22:42,912
NICHOLAS: about theater.

2548
01:22:45,824 --> 01:22:47,776
NICHOLAS: Didn't you have any questions

2549
01:22:47,776 --> 01:22:50,144
NICHOLAS: when I told you that?

2550
01:22:50,700 --> 01:22:53,366
(NICHOLAS talked to his friends about his career path)
SONGHA: When you spoke up...

2551
01:22:53,366 --> 01:22:54,688
NICHOLAS: Suddenly "Why is he saying that?"

2552
01:22:55,500 --> 01:22:58,528
NICHOLAS: I think you might feel that way,
but I'm not sure.

2553
01:22:58,528 --> 01:23:00,466
SONGHA: No, as I've always said,

2554
01:23:00,533 --> 01:23:01,504
SONGHA: I was already thinking about it.

2555
01:23:01,728 --> 01:23:03,968
SONGHA: Anyway, I...

2556
01:23:03,968 --> 01:23:05,632
(NICHOLAS' dream was evident to his friends)
SONGHA: I've watched for a long time

2557
01:23:05,632 --> 01:23:07,200
SONGHA: and thinking about it.

2558
01:23:07,648 --> 01:23:08,896
SONGHA: You must have had a lot of worries.

2559
01:23:08,896 --> 01:23:10,656
NICHOLAS: I did. Really a lot.

2560
01:23:11,104 --> 01:23:15,744
SONGHA: It must have been hard for you to bring it up.

2561
01:23:15,744 --> 01:23:17,568
NICHOLAS: It was so hard to say at that time.

2562
01:23:17,568 --> 01:23:19,648
NICHOLAS: When everyone gathered
in the practice room...

2563
01:23:19,648 --> 01:23:20,832
SONGHA: You really couldn't speak.

2564
01:23:21,216 --> 01:23:22,464
NICHOLAS: I really couldn't.

2565
01:23:23,520 --> 01:23:24,266
SONGHA: Oh, dear.

2566
01:23:24,266 --> 01:23:26,600
NICHOLAS: If I said it after debuting,

2567
01:23:27,466 --> 01:23:29,100
NICHOLAS: being active in the group,

2568
01:23:29,100 --> 01:23:31,500
NICHOLAS: stepping out...

2569
01:23:31,552 --> 01:23:34,300
NICHOLAS: I thought I'd cause too much trouble,

2570
01:23:34,633 --> 01:23:37,800
(That's why he hastily made a decision)
NICHOLAS: So, I chose now.

2571
01:23:38,466 --> 01:23:41,466
NICHOLAS: When I first told them,

2572
01:23:42,166 --> 01:23:43,360
NICHOLAS: their reactions

2573
01:23:43,360 --> 01:23:45,800
NICHOLAS: were better than I expected.

2574
01:23:47,966 --> 01:23:49,600
SONGHA: What did you initially think?

2575
01:23:49,600 --> 01:23:50,400
NICHOLAS: At first, I was kind of...

2576
01:23:50,400 --> 01:23:51,456
SONGHA: You were ready to be criticized, right?

2577
01:23:51,456 --> 01:23:52,736
NICHOLAS: Yeah, ready to be criticized.

2578
01:23:52,736 --> 01:23:54,848
NICHOLAS: I said it after doing it.

2579
01:23:57,333 --> 01:24:01,366
(As his dream became desperate,
he understands the friends' desperation too)

2580
01:24:02,099 --> 01:24:06,233
(The time of worry was long and deep)

2581
01:24:06,833 --> 01:24:08,866
SONGHA: Anyway, you've been at SM,

2582
01:24:08,866 --> 01:24:11,599
SONGHA: at this company, quite a while, right?

2583
01:24:11,599 --> 01:24:14,299
SONGHA: So, you might feel a bit
regretful about the years of training.

2584
01:24:14,299 --> 01:24:16,466
SONGHA: I'm curious about that.

2585
01:24:16,466 --> 01:24:16,832
NICHOLAS: Regretful...

2586
01:24:16,832 --> 01:24:17,184
SONGHA: Regretful...

2587
01:24:17,184 --> 01:24:18,304
NICHOLAS: Are you saying I'm not regretful?

2588
01:24:18,304 --> 01:24:19,168
SONGHA: No, you're not regretful?

2589
01:24:19,299 --> 01:24:21,766
NICHOLAS: I guess I can't really say

2590
01:24:21,766 --> 01:24:24,466
NICHOLAS: I'm not a little regretful...

2591
01:24:24,733 --> 01:24:27,433
NICHOLAS: About not doing it together
with my trainee friends,

2592
01:24:27,433 --> 01:24:29,666
NICHOLAS: I think I'll always regret that.

2593
01:24:30,208 --> 01:24:31,072
NICHOLAS: But

2594
01:24:33,568 --> 01:24:34,880
NICHOLAS: ultimately,

2595
01:24:35,584 --> 01:24:37,152
NICHOLAS: I just need to

2596
01:24:37,152 --> 01:24:40,096
NICHOLAS: make sure I don't regret it later.

2597
01:24:41,216 --> 01:24:41,888
NICHOLAS: That's what I think.

2598
01:24:41,984 --> 01:24:42,720
SONGHA: Of course.

2599
01:24:43,648 --> 01:24:45,866
(At 21, we)
SONGHA: We truly have different paths.

2600
01:24:45,866 --> 01:24:47,488
(now have different goals and dreams)
SONGHA: Right? Your thoughts too.

2601
01:24:49,099 --> 01:24:50,624
SONGHA: We've seen each other since we were minors.

2602
01:24:50,624 --> 01:24:51,168
NICHOLAS: That's right.

2603
01:24:51,360 --> 01:24:52,288
SONGHA: So, somehow...

2604
01:24:52,864 --> 01:24:54,208
SONGHA: We've been watching for a long time.

2605
01:24:54,336 --> 01:24:55,168
SONGHA: I think...

2606
01:24:56,466 --> 01:24:59,699
SONGHA: Not just me, but all the friends here

2607
01:25:01,600 --> 01:25:03,999
SONGHA: will all understand.

2608
01:25:04,333 --> 01:25:06,633
SONGHA: They will support you.

2609
01:25:06,880 --> 01:25:11,066
SONGHA: Of course, we wish for your success.

2610
01:25:11,392 --> 01:25:14,176
SONGHA: So if you feel

2611
01:25:14,176 --> 01:25:15,333
SONGHA: apologetic about it,

2612
01:25:15,566 --> 01:25:16,832
SONGHA: you don't need to be.

2613
01:25:17,699 --> 01:25:20,266
SONGHA: Even though we don't
know exactly how we'll debut,

2614
01:25:20,266 --> 01:25:21,152
SONGHA: once we debut,

2615
01:25:21,344 --> 01:25:23,566
SONGHA: someday, you'll do well, and we'll do well too.

2616
01:25:23,680 --> 01:25:26,666
SONGHA: That's the best picture we can imagine.

2617
01:25:26,666 --> 01:25:28,933
SONGHA: So we end up coming back to film this.

2618
01:25:28,933 --> 01:25:29,888
(Haha)

2619
01:25:30,240 --> 01:25:30,976
NICHOLAS: Reunion.

2620
01:25:31,200 --> 01:25:31,648
SONGHA: Reunion.

2621
01:25:31,648 --> 01:25:32,533
(Let's meet again at WOOJEONG HIGH reunion)
SONGHA: It's a reunion.

2622
01:25:32,533 --> 01:25:33,984
NICHOLAS: It's like a high school reunion.

2623
01:25:34,528 --> 01:25:35,744
NICHOLAS: When we turn 30,

2624
01:25:36,608 --> 01:25:37,760
(The day we meet again a little older)
NICHOLAS: gather together...

2625
01:25:37,792 --> 01:25:39,040
SONGHA: As adults.

2626
01:25:39,328 --> 01:25:40,320
SONGHA: Wouldn't that be amazing?

2627
01:25:42,966 --> 01:25:52,672
(Our dreams for the future
might be a little different from each other)

2628
01:25:54,599 --> 01:26:00,399
(We have the time we spent together now)

2629
01:26:02,133 --> 01:26:04,966
SONGHA: And after this, up until the fan meeting...

2630
01:26:04,966 --> 01:26:05,504
NICHOLAS: Right.

2631
01:26:05,504 --> 01:26:07,233
SONGHA: We'll be doing it together.

2632
01:26:07,456 --> 01:26:08,992
SONGHA: So until then,

2633
01:26:09,216 --> 01:26:10,999
SONGHA: let's really give it our all.

2634
01:26:10,999 --> 01:26:12,064
SONGHA: Let's keep going

2635
01:26:12,064 --> 01:26:15,233
SONGHA: until May next year.

2636
01:26:19,933 --> 01:26:23,733
(And on that day, in NICHOLAS' diary)

2637
01:26:25,024 --> 01:26:28,866
(Only emotions beyond words remain)

2638
01:26:29,952 --> 01:26:30,272
(Next Episode Preview)

2639
01:26:30,272 --> 01:26:32,299
(Finally)
ALL: Five boys!

2640
01:26:32,640 --> 01:26:36,133
(WOOJEONG HIGH students went outside)

2641
01:26:36,833 --> 01:26:37,760
HYUNJUN: Hello.

2642
01:26:38,080 --> 01:26:40,256
HYUNJUN: Today is 1996,

2643
01:26:40,256 --> 01:26:42,016
HYUNJUN: September 30.

2644
01:26:42,016 --> 01:26:43,552
(90s On)
HYUNJUN: You're the champ of caps today!

2645
01:26:44,000 --> 01:26:44,896
HYUNJUN: You are awesome today.

2646
01:26:45,533 --> 01:26:46,720
(Enjoying with a return to the '90s)
HYUNJUN: I hope it comes out like this.

2647
01:26:47,136 --> 01:26:48,448
HYUNJUN: Kind of holding it...

2648
01:26:48,966 --> 01:26:49,568
(One-day school field trip)

2649
01:26:49,568 --> 01:26:50,560
- TRAINEE: Why are we so excited?
- HYUNJUN: Hey, hey, hey.

2650
01:26:52,672 --> 01:26:53,856
HANBI: Holding a drawing pot.

2651
01:26:55,099 --> 01:26:57,799
(Class '00 in the sketch contest, Five Boys Over Flowers)
TRAINEE: Hi.

2652
01:26:58,592 --> 01:27:00,832
(Under the warm light, drawing my friend's face)

2653
01:27:04,166 --> 01:27:06,033
(Eyes, nose, mouth count look alike)

2654
01:27:06,033 --> 01:27:06,866
SADAHARU: Mouth.

2655
01:27:06,866 --> 01:27:09,033
(Time to heal outside the classroom)

2656
01:27:09,344 --> 01:27:11,233
SONGHA: Oh, it's ruined!

2657
01:27:11,360 --> 01:27:12,352
SADAHARU: Is this me?

2658
01:27:15,999 --> 01:27:17,760
(The masterpiece drawn by SONGHA, who suffered alone)
SONGHA: I think it's in the top 3 of the best drawings

2659
01:27:17,760 --> 01:27:19,040
SONGHA: I've ever made in my life.

2660
01:27:19,456 --> 01:27:20,099
SONGHA: Really!

2661
01:27:20,099 --> 01:27:20,799
(SONGHA's drawing)
SADAHARU: Three points!

2662
01:27:22,560 --> 01:27:24,448
SADAHARU: We don't change the three points.

2663
01:27:25,833 --> 01:27:28,266
(Class '10, WONHA~JANNI on a school field trip)

2664
01:27:28,544 --> 01:27:29,312
HAMIN: Hold on.

2665
01:27:30,166 --> 01:27:32,133
(For someone, it's a courage experience)
TRAINEE: Looking at this, it feels like I could die!

2666
01:27:32,533 --> 01:27:33,696
(Various experience learning to develop cooperation)

2667
01:27:33,696 --> 01:27:35,488
DANIEL: Over here.

2668
01:27:35,966 --> 01:27:39,399
(Handle the entire Busan tour from the bus in one go)
HARUTA: Wow, hurry up.

2669
01:27:39,766 --> 01:27:41,299
DANIEL: Isn't it Busan!

2670
01:27:41,299 --> 01:27:43,136
DANIEL: How long are you going to stay like this?

2671
01:27:43,599 --> 01:27:44,733
DANIEL: Do you want to just live there?

2672
01:27:44,899 --> 01:27:46,266
(Become a master of hanging)

2673
01:27:46,266 --> 01:27:47,968
TRAINEE: I want to be buried here someday too.

2674
01:27:48,899 --> 01:27:50,880
WOOLIN: When you're buried here,
you seem like a great person!

2675
01:27:50,880 --> 01:27:51,699
TRAINEE: That's right.

2676
01:27:51,699 --> 01:27:53,466
WOOLIN: I have to come here naturally.

